The paper proposes a new policy search algorithm for constrained reinforcement learning, which involves training neural network policies for high-dimensional control while making guarantees about policy behavior throughout training. This work is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), robotics (cs.RO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), systems and control (cs.SY), and computer vision (cs.CV).
